<subSubSection id="C34F25F2FF902E2476DECC20FA1EF90D" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEA7679FF902E2476DECC20FB2FF921" blockId="9.[151,1437,1571,2030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B921AA6BFF902E2476DECC20FE90F99A" bold="true" box="[151,274,1571,1597]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shell ovate-conic, pale brown with slightly convex whorls. Aperture ovate, usually appressed to body whorl. Mantle tissue pigmented reddish. Rounded median cusp of central radular teeth. Penial gland does not bifurcate at proximal end, terminal gland of the penis extending to ventral and dorsal aspects.
</paragraph>
