<subSubSection id="C34F25F2FF902E24768ECCDBFB00F8B2" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEA7679FF902E24768ECCDBFB00F8B2" blockId="9.[151,1437,1571,2030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B921AA6BFF902E24768ECCDBFECCF955" bold="true" box="[199,334,1752,1778]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">Etymology.</emphasis>
We use the specific epithet “rubra” to refer to both the reddish pigmentation on the tissues of this snail and the red volcanic rock faces in the high canyon walls and surrounding landscape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F25F2FF902E24768ECD23FB7CF8FA" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
