</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F25F2FF902E20768ECD64FCCDFEC2" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEA7679FF902E27768ECD64FD28FF5D" blockId="9.[151,1437,1571,2030]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,250]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B921AA6BFF902E24768ECD64FEDBF826" bold="true" box="[199,345,1895,1921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393">Description.</emphasis>
Shell ovate-conic, very pale brown in color, taller spire with slightly convex and shouldered whorls. Protoconch uneroded, mostly smooth with scattered raised granules. Teleoconch with strong growth lines. Aperture ovate, angled above, nearly appressed to body whorl. Peristome complete, inner lip slightly thickened. Outer lip prosocline, simple. Narrowly umbilicate. Average shell measurements for n= 
<specimenCount id="9D53BDF0FF902E2475B9CDD7FBCBF84A" box="[1008,1097,2003,2030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" type="adult">10 adult</specimenCount>
individuals: shell height= 
<quantity id="4CADDB9CFF902E277322CDD0FF41FF16" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="394" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.49" pageId="9" pageNumber="393" unit="mm" value="2.49">2.49 mm</quantity>
